util.config.props

Interface JPropSetter<T>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    JPropAccessor

    public interface JPropSetter<T>
    Encapsulates the setting of a typed property to a Java Properties store.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • set

        void set(java.util.Properties db,
         T value)
        Sets the property value to be the string representation of the given typed value.
        Parameters:
        db - the Properties store.
        value - the value to set after converting it to its string representation. The value must not be null or an exception will be thrown; if you really need to set an empty value use the setEmpty method.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any argument is null.

      • setEmpty

        Parameters:
        db - the Properties store.

      • remove

        java.util.Optional<java.lang.String> remove(java.util.Properties db)
        Removes the property from the store
        Parameters:
        db - the Properties store.
        Returns:
        the property string value if the property was found and deleted; empty if the property was not found.
